# Currency Storage Rules

## Core Principle
All monetary values (prices, balances, P&L) are stored in **cents** internally. Convert to dollars only at the display layer.

## Data Flow
1. **Kalshi API** returns centi-cents (1/100 of a cent)
2. **Position stream** converts to cents (`/ 100`)
3. **TradingContext** stores everything in cents
4. **Display components** use `formatDollars()` to show dollars

## Formatting Utilities

Import from `@/utils/formatCurrency`:

```typescript
import { formatDollars, formatDollarsWithSign, formatCents } from '@/utils/formatCurrency';

formatDollars(1234)        // → "$12.34"
formatDollarsWithSign(1234) // → "+$12.34"
formatDollarsWithSign(-500) // → "-$5.00"
formatCents(67)            // → "67¢"
```

## Examples

❌ **BAD**: Storing dollars, converting at ingestion
```typescript
setState({ balance: kalshiBalance.balance / 100 }); // Converts to dollars
<Text>${balance.toFixed(2)}</Text>
```

✅ **GOOD**: Storing cents, converting at display
```typescript
setState({ balance: kalshiBalance.balance }); // Already cents
<Text>{formatDollars(balance)}</Text>
```

❌ **BAD**: Inline dollar formatting
```typescript
<Text>{pnl >= 0 ? '+' : ''}${pnl.toFixed(2)}</Text>
```

✅ **GOOD**: Using format utilities
```typescript
<Text>{formatDollarsWithSign(pnl)}</Text>
```

## Interface Documentation

Always document monetary fields with their unit:

```typescript
interface Position {
  entryPrice: number;    // cents per contract
  currentPrice: number;  // cents per contract
  pnl: number;           // cents
}
```
